{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Snapshots","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Snapshots"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"SnapshotManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the VM’s disk image ("},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"code":"auxiliary.bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), and machine identifier ("},{"code":"machine-identifier.bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stored in a named subdirectory under the bundle’s "},{"code":"SavedStates\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How Snapshots Work","anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The VM "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}]},{"type":"text","text":" before saving or restoring."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the snapshot copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write","text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileManager.copyItem"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which the system maps to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clonefile(2)"},{"text":". This produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consume additional storage.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","type":"heading"},{"syntax":null,"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── machine-identifier.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   ├── machine-identifier.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        ├── machine-identifier.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Example","